\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 160. C. sulphurea} Willd.,{\i  Enum. Pl. Horti Berol.} 930 (1809). Annual. Stems 30-50 cm, erect, divaricately branched above, narrowly winged, leafy almost to apex. Leaves linear to linear-lanceolate or the lower lyrate-pinnatifid, sparsely lanate; lower petiolate; upper sessile. Involucre (12-)15-20 mm in diameter, ovoid-conical; bracts ovate, sparsely lanate to subglabrous; appendages not decurrent, semiorbicular, with slender, patent, dark purple apical spine 15-20 mm and very slender lateral spines 5-6 mm; appendages of outer bracts with subequal, whitish spines 7-8 mm. Florets yellow, glandular. Achenes c. 4·5 mm; pappus c. 2 mm, brownish.{\i  Disturbed or rocky ground. S. & S.E. Spain}. Hs.
\par 

