\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 161. C. nicaeensis} All.,{\i  Fl. Pedem.}{\b  1}: 162 (1785). Biennial. Stems 30-60 cm, erect, virgately branched above, not winged. Lower leaves lyrate-pinnatifid; upper oblong, cordate, semiamplexicaul; uppermost oblong to lanceolate. Capitula solitary, surrounded by upper leaves. Involucre 12-18 mm in diameter, ovoid; bracts glabrous; appendages not decurrent, with apical spine 10-15 mm and 2-3 short lateral spines on each side. Florets yellow. Achenes c. 4·5 mm; pappus 1-1·5 mm.{\i  Cultivated or waste ground. W. & C. Mediterranean region eastwards to Malta.} Hs It Sa Si
